{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a55ab3b1-6bad-46e0-b9c5-96196b54e9ff","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed**. That property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge. You can simply remove it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_016Rucps676FJPXxsbQD7ktx","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_011pX5AFeobJWUb8axc4Bb2Z","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7a69983e64f748a3b0198ffc236449a5/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7a69983e64f748a3b0198ffc236449a5/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"41c3cc2c-12bc-4bda-bce7-13f16de056e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native Microsoft.Testing.Platform support built-in, so the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed.\n\nIn .NET 10, the SDK ships with a new `dotnet test` that natively integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The key changes:\n\n1. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed — it was a bridge property for .NET 9 to opt into MTP via `dotnet test`. In .NET 10, this is the default behavior.\n\n\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` should stay enabled since it activates the MSTest runner built on MTP, and `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform` might be set automatically in .NET 10 or can be explicitly configured if needed.\n\n3. Since .NET 10 has MTP integration built-in by default, I should remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property entirely as it's no longer required.","outputTokens":621},"id":"26da6d43-491f-4742-b081-1e8637c4224f","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:07.583Z","parentId":"e1abe669-4774-417d-9816-6415e07